name: Is a dragonfly
description: After reading a bit, I conclude that this insect is a dragonfly, not a damselfly. These are not the same insects, but they are related.  There are four details that even the most inexperienced bug watcher can use to identify if the insect is a dragonfly or a damselfly. They are the eyes, body shape, wing shape, and position of the wings at rest.
